Paper: hep-th/0211024

Date: 2002-11-05

Title: Quasinormal modes for massless topological black holes

Authors: Rodrigo Aros, Cristian Martinez, Ricardo Troncoso and Jorge Zanelli

Comments: CECS style, 10 pages, no figures

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D67 (2003) 044014

An exact expression for the quasinormal modes of a scalar perturbation on amassless topological black hole in four and higher dimensions is presented. Themassive scalar field is nonminimally coupled to the curvature, and the horizongeometry is assumed to have negative constant curvature.